SIMPLE: bocardo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bocardo
<hw>Bo*car"do</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A mnemonic
word.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>A form of syllogism of
which the first and third propositions are particular negatives, and the
middle term a universal affirmative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Baroko and <qex>Bocardo</qex> have been stumbling blocks to the
logicians.</q> <rj><qau>Bowen.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A prison; -- originally the name of the old north
gate in Oxford, which was used as a prison.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Latimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bocasine</ent>⟦br⟧
